        {
          "name": "Job Details",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/public/jobs/{{job_id}}",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "public",
                "jobs",
                "{{job_id}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "#### Purpose\nRetrieve details for a single public job posting by its ID.\n\n---\n#### Endpoint\n`GET {{base_url}}/api/public/jobs/{{job_id}}`\n\n- **Method:** `GET`\n- **Auth:** **Public** (No authentication required)\n\n---\n#### Variables\n**Base URL**\n- `{{base_url}}` — API host (for example `http://localhost`)\n\n**Path variable**\n- `{{job_id}}` — The job identifier to fetch details for.\n\n---\n#### Example request\n```http\nGET {{base_url}}/api/public/jobs/{{job_id}}\n```\n\n---\n#### Possible responses\n**200 OK** — Job found; returns job details.\n\n**404 Not Found** — No job exists for the provided `job_id`.\n\n**422 Unprocessable Entity** — Validation error (for example, `job_id` is missing/invalid).\n\n---\n#### Example response shape (200)\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": 1,\n  \"title\": \"Software Engineer\",\n  \"company\": \"Acme Inc\",\n  \"location\": \"Remote\",\n  \"employment_type\": \"Full-time\",\n  \"description\": \"...\",\n  \"skills\": [\"JavaScript\", \"Node.js\"],\n  \"status\": \"open\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-01-01T12:00:00Z\",\n  \"updated_at\": \"2026-01-02T12:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n> Note: Field names may vary based on your backend implementation; use the response returned by your API as the source of truth."
          },
          "response": []
        },
